cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper is about a new deep learning architecture for Natural Language Inference (NLI), which is a subfield of computational linguistics and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the design of a conceptually simple, compact, and powerful model, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The use of factorization layers for efficient and expressive compression of alignment vectors may also indicate a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the visual analysis of the propagated features suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
